Package: DGQ
Type: Package
Title: Dynamic Geometric Quantiles for Multivariate Time Series
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Lizhong", "Chen", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "nealforeverfriend@gmail.com"),
    person("Xueming", "Li", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Computes the Dynamic Geometric Quantile (DGQ) for collections of
    multivariate time series, extending the empirical dynamic quantile of
    Pena, Tsay and Zamar (2019) <doi:10.1080/00401706.2019.1575285> to the
    multivariate setting via Chaudhuri's (1996) geometric quantile
    <doi:10.2307/2291681>. A single entry point, DGQ(), returns both the
    unconstrained time-wise geometric quantile (a free trajectory) and the
    constrained empirical DGQ (a real observed series) for one or more tilt
    directions. Supports raw Euclidean, pooled-whitening Mahalanobis, and
    per-time Mahalanobis metrics, exact or CLARA-subsampled depth, and accepts
    either a 3-D array or a list of matrices. The numerically heavy core is
    implemented in C through the R C interface.
